  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Connecting Communities:Learning for Life</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A quarter of 15-24 year-olds in Zambia have never been to school. Many orphans don&#x2019;t finish basic education or go to high school, especially if they are girls. This project trains committees to identify 14-16 year-olds not in school and those who may drop out. Vulnerable young people are encouraged to work with the committees to set up clubs that provide business skills, homework help and drama and sports activities. Together, they lobby for better government services. The neediest families receive money for school fees and materials, as well as being helped to develop money earning initiatives. As a result, more young people finish school, and both they and their families have a higher chance of getting work.</narrative>
  </description>
